{"parts":[{"text":"For context:"},{"text":"[jarvis_root_agent] said: I have access to a variety of tools and can delegate to specialized agents to assist you. Here's a detailed description:\n\n### **Tools:**\n\n1.  **`get_current_datetime`**\n    *   **Description:** This tool allows me to retrieve the current date, time, and day of the week.\n\n2.  **`expense_tracker tools`**\n    *   **Description:** A suite of tools designed for managing financial expenses.\n        *   `add_expense_tool`: Records a new expense with details like date, amount, category, and notes.\n        *   `edit_expense_tool`: Modifies an existing expense record using its ID.\n        *   `delete_expense_tool`: Removes an expense record by its ID.\n        *   `search_expenses_tool`: Helps find expenses based on various filters such as category, date range, or amount range.\n\n3.  **`to_do tools`**\n    *   **Description:** A set of tools for task and reminder management.\n        *   `add_task_tool`: Creates a new task with a title, description, due date, and priority.\n        *   `edit_task_tool`: Updates details of an existing task like its title, description, due date, priority, or status.\n        *   `delete_task_tool`: Deletes a task by its ID.\n        *   `complete_task_tool`: Marks a specific task as completed.\n        *   `search_tasks_tool`: Allows searching for tasks using filters like due date, priority, or status.\n\n4.  **`file_system tools`**\n    *   **Description:** A comprehensive set of tools for interacting with the local file system, enabling file and folder management.\n        *   `read_file_tool`: Reads the content of a specified file.\n        *   `write_file_tool`: Writes content to a specified file, overwriting existing content if any.\n        *   `edit_file_tool`: Finds and replaces specific text within a file.\n        *   `append_file_tool`: Adds content to the end of a specified file.\n        *   `copy_file_tool`: Duplicates a file from a source path to a destination path.\n        *   `move_file_tool`: Relocates a file from one path to another.\n        *   `delete_file_tool`: Removes a specified file.\n        *   `clear_file_tool`: Empties the content of a specified file.\n        *   `create_directory_tool`: Creates a new folder at a given path.\n        *   `delete_directory_tool`: Deletes a specified folder, with an option for recursive deletion.\n        *   `rename_directory_tool`: Renames a folder or moves it to a new location.\n        *   `list_files_tool`: Lists all files within a specified folder.\n        *   `list_directories_tool`: Lists all subdirectories within a specified folder.\n        *   `list_tree_tool`: Provides a hierarchical view of files and directories within a specified folder up to a certain depth.\n        *   `file_info_tool`: Retrieves information about a specified file.\n        *   `supported_formats_tool`: Lists the file formats supported by the file system tools (though this specific tool's function details are not explicitly provided, it implies capabilities around various file types).\n\n### **Agents:**\n\n1.  **`research_agent`**\n    *   **Description:** This agent is specialized in performing deep research. It can conduct parallel web searches to gather live data and compile it into a structured report. Use this for complex research questions or when you need the latest information on a topic.\n\n2.  **`problem_solver_agent`**\n    *   **Description:** This agent is designed to analyze and solve technical issues. It can diagnose programming errors, exceptions, stack traces, bugs, crashes, configuration problems, and other technical issues. It identifies root causes using Google Search and its knowledge base, then provides step-by-step solutions for fixing them. I will transfer to this agent whenever you present an error message, bug report, or any technical problem requiring debugging."}],"role":"user"}
